criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  BMI between 30 and 45

          -  with biopsy-proven NASH

          -  with or without type 2 diabetes

          -  that fit for bariatric surgery.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  borderline NASH ou cirrhosis;

          -  alcohol consumption (> 20 g/day for men and > 10 g/day for women, for the last 2
             years);

          -  other hepatic diseases (such as viral hepatitis, autoimmune hepatitis, drug-induced
             hepatic disease, Wilson's disease, hemochromatosis);

          -  HIV infection;

          -  unable to provide informed consent;

          -  previous foregut or bariatric surgery;

          -  malignancy;

          -  patients that unfit for bariatric surgery.
